{
  "text": "With time, L(t) approaches the horizontal asymptote F/s, as illustrated in Fig. 1 b (continuously black curves). If F exceeds F th and is not too large (the limit is specified below), then a tether initially extends according to Eq. 3, until it undergoes a crossover. The work of Shao et al. [CITATION_1] demonstrates that after crossover a tether pulled by a constant force extends linearly, i.e., _",
